 A) No, water does not freeze at -12 degrees Celsius. Water freezes at 0 degrees Celsius under standard atmospheric pressure.

B) If a glass of pure water is cooled down to -12 degrees Celsius, it will remain in its liquid state. It will not freeze because it is below the freezing point of water. However, it will become colder and denser as it approaches the freezing point. [end of text]


